Longitudinal smoothers in R

How to use smoothing functions in R with {ggplot}

Jordan Gauthier https://github.com/drjgauthier (Fred Hutch/University of Washington)
2021-11-08

Contents

Simulate data with ordinal scale over time

Show code 
library(tidyverse)
#Time points
t <- c(0:28)

#Favorable trajectory
y1 <- round(sin(t/7)*4+4)
plot(t,y1)
Show code 
#Unfavorable trajectory
y2 <- round(sin(t/15)*4+3)
plot(t,y2)
Show code 
#Simulate 100 patients for each trajectory
d1 <- data.frame()
for (i in 1:100) { 
  tmp <- round(sin(t/7)*4+4) + runif(1,-1,1)
  d1 <- rbind(d1, tmp)
 }
colnames(d1) <- c(0:28)
d1$traj <- "traj1"
d1$pt <- c(0:99)

d2 <-  data.frame()
for (i in 1:100) { 
  tmp <- round(sin(t/15)*4+3)+ runif(1,-1,1)
  d2 <- rbind(d2, tmp)
}
colnames(d2) <- c(0:28)
d2$traj <- "traj2"
d2$pt <- c(100:199)
d <- bind_rows(d1,d2)

Plot patient trajectories

Show code 
d %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(`0`:`28`),
               names_to = "tp",
               values_to = "grade") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = as.numeric(tp), y = grade, group = as.character(pt),col=traj)) +
  geom_line(alpha=0.2) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0:28))+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0:10))+
  theme_bw()

Plot patient trajectories - LOESS Smoother

Show code 
d %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(`0`:`28`),
               names_to = "tp",
               values_to = "grade") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = as.numeric(tp), y = grade, group = as.character(pt),col=traj)) +
  geom_line(alpha=0.2) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0:28))+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0:10))+
  theme_bw() +
  geom_smooth(aes(group=traj),method = "loess",se=T)

Plot patient trajectories - B-spline

Show code 
d %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(`0`:`28`),
               names_to = "tp",
               values_to = "grade") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = as.numeric(tp), y = grade, group = as.character(pt),col=traj)) +
  geom_line(alpha=0.2) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0:28))+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0:10))+
  theme_bw() +
  geom_smooth(aes(group=traj),method = lm, formula = y ~ splines::bs(x, 3))

Plot patient trajectories - natural spline

Show code 
d %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(`0`:`28`),
               names_to = "tp",
               values_to = "grade") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = as.numeric(tp), y = grade, group = as.character(pt),col=traj)) +
  geom_line(alpha=0.2) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0:28))+
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0:10))+
  theme_bw() +
  geom_smooth(aes(group=traj),method = lm, formula = y ~ splines::ns(x, 3))
